Introduction

Park Ji Eun, more popularly known mononymously as Jieun, is a South Korean singer. She was the vocalist and visual of RBW's girl group PURPLE KISS. She rose to fame after joining Mnet’s hit survival show, Produce 48 where she finished 80th.

She debuted with PURPLE KISS on March 15, 2021, with the mini album “INTO VIOLET”, with the title track “Ponzona”.

On November 18, 2022, RBW announced that Park Ji Eun decided to end her activities with PURPLE KISS due to physical and mental health issues.
